Coding Guidelines:
  ☐ unit testing (with "catch")
  ☐ raii, smart pointers
  ☐ SOLID https://github.com/ryanmcdermott/clean-code-javascript#solid
  ☐ overload when you can, specialise when you need to.
  ☐ if you know that an entity must take a certain kind of ownership of the object, always use smart pointers
  ☐ ifstream more modular than fopen https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6399822/reading-a-text-file-fopen-vs-ifstream
  ☐ class vs namespace. namespace: to group functions, better than static class. Also to avoid duplicate class names. class: A class is a group of variables and procedures that are related to each other
  ☐ can not pass 2d array in parameter    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27892464/c-return-value-type-does-not-match-the-function-type
  ☐ template vs inheritance: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7264402/when-to-use-template-vs-inheritance
  ☐ template class error (unresolved external symbol): Templates must be defined in header files https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5776862/template-class-unresolved-external-symbols
  ☐ avoid allocating on the heap if possible. use Foo foo = Foo() instead of new Foo(). Reasons: RAII, it's faster on the stack, no memory management. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6500313/why-should-c-programmers-minimize-use-of-new    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/7973138/how-do-i-choose-heap-allocation-vs-stack-allocation-in-c    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11477523/when-and-why-to-declare-member-variables-on-the-heap-c
  ☐ init vs constructor https://softwareengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/175594/c-constructor-or-initialize-method-to-startup
  ☐ in C++, never use malloc, use new. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/184537/in-what-cases-do-i-use-malloc-vs-new
  ☐ Mat vs IplImage https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3232022/opencv-iplimage-versus-mat-which-to-use
  ☐ Builder vs Factory https://stackoverflow.com/questions/757743/what-is-the-difference-between-builder-design-pattern-and-factory-design-pattern
  ☐ public const vs getter https://stackoverflow.com/a/4984708/6689201 use public members for "immutable data classes", use getters for "behaviour classes" and "mutable data classes": https://stackoverflow.com/a/32625408/6689201
  ☐ Can't open file name: put the name of the file


